// contentStatus.js — GSL machine-readable module pipeline status (companion to
// moduleTiers.js). Single source of truth for "has this module completed the full
// writer -> Pass-2 blind adversarial audit" per 3B1B-STANDARD.md's Enforcement
// process. moduleTiers.js answers WHICH modules exist and their interview tier; this
// file answers WHERE each one currently is in the content-quality pipeline.
// GSL_PLAN.md remains the narrative history (what happened, why, what was found) --
// this file is the queryable CURRENT STATE, generated by seeding every TIER_S/TIER_A
// moduleId from moduleTiers.js (so no module can be silently dropped) and only
// overriding to a real status where independently verified.
//
// Status values:
//   'unclassified' -- predates this file (created 2026-07-11); status genuinely
//                     unknown, do not infer done or not-done from its absence here.
//   'pending'       -- confirmed not yet started.
//   'in_progress'   -- writer pass started, audit loop not yet closed.
//   'clean'         -- writer + Pass-2 adversarial audit both complete, confirmed PASS
//                     (or closed at the 3-round cap with the final small items fixed
//                     and independently re-verified).
//
// HARD RULE (see CLAUDE.md's 2026-07-10 Recordkeeping section): never set a module's
// status to 'clean' from memory of a prior summary sentence. Only set it in the same
// edit where you have just personally verified it -- grepped the live file, or read
// the audit agent's actual PASS output this turn. A wrong 'clean' here is worse than
// no entry at all, because the whole point of this file is that it can be trusted
// without re-deriving. Seeded 2026-07-11 with only the modules verified in the
// GSL Retrieval A/B (Batches 7-8) and Evaluation & Judgment (Batch 9) rounds --
// every other S/A-tier module is honestly 'unclassified', not backfilled from
// unverified memory of earlier batch logs.
//
// SCHEMA RULE, enforced by convention (no build-time check exists yet -- see
// CLAUDE.md if one gets added): any entry with status: 'clean' MUST include a
// `verifiedBy` string field. It is not optional prose color, it's the receipt. It
// must contain, concretely:
//   1. The IST timestamp the check was actually run (not the batch date -- the
//      moment THIS specific verification happened).
//   2. A re-runnable check: an exact grep pattern + file path, an exact shell
//      command (esbuild/node --check + its exit status), or an exact file:line
//      citation -- something a skeptical future reader could redo in under a
//      minute, not "an agent confirmed it."
//   3. What that check actually confirmed, in specific terms (which sentence,
//      which number, which behavior) -- not the bare word "verified."
// A `status: 'clean'` entry with no `verifiedBy`, or one that's just the word
// "verified" / "confirmed" with nothing re-runnable, should be treated as
// untrustworthy as an 'unclassified' entry -- worse, actually, since it's
// actively claiming confidence it hasn't earned.

